Distribution. Previously this species was reported from Greece , Turkey , Syria , Israel and Iran ( Chatzaki 2010 ;
Zamani et al . 2020
). New records from Tajikistan represent the easternmost localities of this species.

Comments.
Recorded from 
Tajikistan
for the first time; apparently, 

N. palaestina

is common and widespread in south-western regions of the country (
Khatlon Region
) (
Figs 65–66
).
